{
  "article_id": "TheWorld1899",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "AN expedition is being organized in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California",
        "entity_key": "re_socal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the purpose of exploring and making a scientific report on"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the most remarkable island off the"
      },
      {
        "text": "California coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "When this task is performed it may be possible to fill up the gaps in the meagre but marvellous story of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Maria Better Than Nothing, the wild woman of the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Maria's bones now rest in"
      },
      {
        "text": "holy ground",
        "entity_key": "sbmissioncemetary",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She was buried by"
      },
      {
        "text": "the mission in Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and"
      },
      {
        "text": "the good fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "prayed over her body. If this was praiseworthy of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the monks",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", there was in it also a certain appropriateness, for it was due to"
      },
      {
        "text": "a particularly zealous group of Franciscan Fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that"
      },
      {
        "text": "Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "came to suffer her long and terrible isolation."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Here is the Wild Woman's story precisely as any of the good people of",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "will tell it to you:",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Many years ago it came to the knowledge of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the pious monks of the southern coast",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that on"
      },
      {
        "text": "a barren island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", twelve miles long and four wide, lying some seventy miles away, there dwelt"
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe of Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "who knew little of civilization and nothing of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Church",
        "entity_key": "ch_catholic",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "This desert spot",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", wind-swept, wave-beaten, with no harbors and sparse vegetation, seemed to"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Franciscans",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "ill-adapted for permanent missionary work. So they made the astonishing determination to carry off"
      },
      {
        "text": "the entire population of the island",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and divide it among"
      },
      {
        "text": "the missions of the coast",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "A ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was fitted up and set sail."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In the face of almost hopeless obstacles"
      },
      {
        "text": "the missionaries",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", having succeeded in anchoring"
      },
      {
        "text": "their ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "off the hilly side of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", forced friendly overtures upon"
      },
      {
        "text": "the desert tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and at length persuaded"
      },
      {
        "text": "the hundred natives",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to leave"
      },
      {
        "text": "their sterile soil",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and embark for"
      },
      {
        "text": "the land of sunshine and abundant produce",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On the day of embarkation a gale swept fiercely across"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "The ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "heaved restlessly, tugging at her anchor."
      },
      {
        "text": "The captain",
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was about to give the order to set sail when"
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the women",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered that"
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been left on shore. It was too late."
      },
      {
        "text": "The vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "could no longer resist the gale and her anchor was hauled in with all haste. But the woman's maternal passion could not be thwarted."
      },
      {
        "text": "In a frenzy she leaped from",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "and swam back through the surf to the shore.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Now for twenty years nothing was known of"
      },
      {
        "text": "this poor creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". There was so little likelihood that she had survived that the responsibility of her rescue did not weigh heavily on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the good fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had, indeed, all that they could do in caring for and converting"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians they had already imported",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "The captain",
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who had been forced to abandon"
      },
      {
        "text": "the young mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", had promised, it is true, to return for her, but"
      },
      {
        "text": "his ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was afterward wrecked."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After twenty years the oft-repeated story of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the foresaken woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "reached the ears of a warm-hearted and adventurous"
      },
      {
        "text": "young priest",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He enlisted the services of an"
      },
      {
        "text": "otter hunter",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "several Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who, in a small schooner known as"
      },
      {
        "text": "Better Than Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", set sail for"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which had in the mean time been christened"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "There they found"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Not at first, because she had seen their approach and, timid as a deer, avoided them. A bunch of dried herbs and the smoldering ashes of a fire betrayed her presence on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". And after a well-planned search they came upon"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who had not seen a human face in twenty years."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She was a startling picture, with staring eyes and unkempt hair and wearing the strangest costume ever seen on a woman.",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "From neck to ankle she was decorously enveloped in a single, marvellously contrived garment of birds' skins, forming a brilliant patchwork of feathers. Her pitiful desire to be decently garbed, though abandoned and unseen, had been accomplished by years of painstaking labor. A dress of birds' skins is not made in a day. About her shoulders—for the winds of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are chilly—was a garment of sealskin.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Her slender, woman's hands had constructed the brush hut before which she was sitting when the sailors found her. With the cunning of a wild thing she had built this hut in a canyon and had placed about it a windbreak of whalebone and strong twigs.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She smiled in unmeaning fashion when",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the men",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "approached, and began to make strange wordless sounds.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The Indians of the party",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", thinking her more than human, fell down to worship her.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The others",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "tried to communicate with her by sign, but",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor wild woman",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "understood nothing.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "But although she had come to share many characteristics of a wild animal, she had retained a curious gentleness of disposition. Therefore,",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the adventurers",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were able to persuade her to leave her hut and board",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "with them, after consenting that she should bring with her a tame otter to which she clung with savage fondness.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When they had brought her to",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "some Indians succeeded in drawing from",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the poor woman",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "fragments of information about her appalling experience. But memory had almost left poor",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Maria Better Than Nothing",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", as they had named her, after",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "that rescued her.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The baby",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "for whom she had risked her life was shortly after torn to death by dogs, and doubtless the grief which",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the young mother",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "suffered because of this wrecked her mind.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For a long time she was ill and wanted to die, but instinct of self-preservation kept her alive and she lived on painfully year after year, making friends of the few animals on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "until"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Better Than Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "found her."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Accustomed as she had become to a wild life,",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Maria",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "could not resist the weakening influences of civilization. In less than three months",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the \"wild woman\"",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "died, mourning to the very last",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the baby",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that had died a score of years before.",
        "tropes": [
          3,
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Maria's remarkable dress of feathers was afterward sent to"
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for preservation in"
      },
      {
        "text": "the great museum of the Propaganda",
        "entity_key": "mu_vaticanmuseum",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  ]
}